    • getAllEFormsExpectFdid

      public List<EFormData> getAllEFormsExpectFdid(LoggedInInfo loggedInInfo, Integer demographicNo, Integer fdid)
      This method is intended for use in the attachment window (attachDocument.jsp) and is designed to retrieve a list of eForms except one. In other parts of the application, developers are encouraged to use EFormUtil.listPatientEformsCurrent() to access all available eForms. The reason for this function is to ensure a user cannot attach an eForm to itself.
      Specified by:
      getAllEFormsExpectFdid in interface DocumentAttachmentManager
